.Im MicroEmacs command|window
.ds C0 "(\fB\*e\*cv\fR)\ \&
.ds C1 "(\fB\*e\*cz\fR)\ \&
.so me.tni
.TH scroll-next-window-down 2
.XI scroll-next-window-down - "\*(C0Scroll next window down"
.XI scroll-next-window-up - "\*(C1Scroll next window up"
.SH NAME
.Me "|scroll-next-window-down"
scroll-next-window-down \- Scroll next window down
.br
.Me "|scroll-next-window-up"
scroll-next-window-up \- Scroll next window up
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.I n
\fBscroll-next-window-down\fR \*(C0
.br
.I n
\fBscroll-next-window-up\fR \*(C1
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B scroll-next-window-down
scrolls  the next window down  \fIn\fR  lines, if \fIn\fR is omitted  then the
next  window is  scrolled  by  \fIwindow\fR  number of lines (i.e. next screen
page).
.PP
.B scroll-next-window-up
scrolls the next window up \fIn\fR lines, as
.BR scroll-next-window-down .
.PP
These commands are useful in macros to control other windows.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
